{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897713569,"sessionID":"ses_2843f9435ffeZ3zCsY9nzwDCy7","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc09b770012mG1WGMkBhhj08","messageID":"msg_d7bc08d1e001WTiCfeDOh75HX2","sessionID":"ses_2843f9435ffeZ3zCsY9nzwDCy7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-baf1b952970841ad946d3c413c783f33","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Integrations вҖ” Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n4: \n5: ## Dify plugin вҖ” file map\n6: \n7: | File | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n10: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n11: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n12: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n13: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n14: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n15: | `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n16: | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n17: \n18: ## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n19: \n20: From source:\n21: \n22: - `version`: `0.0.2`\n23: - `type`: `plugin`\n24: - `author`: `volcano-sh`\n25: - `name`: `agentcube`\n26: - `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` вҶ’ `Agentcube`\n27: - `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n28: - `icon`: `icon.png`\n29: - `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n30: - `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n31: - `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n32: - `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n33: - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n34: \n35: ## `provider/agentcube.yaml` structure\n36: \n37: - `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n38: - Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n39: - `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n40: - `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n41: \n42: ## Tool definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n43: \n44: - `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n45: - `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n46: - `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n47: - `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n48: \n49: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n50: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n51: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n52: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n53: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n54: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n55: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n56: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n57: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n58: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n59: \n60: - `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n61: \n62: ## Provider implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n63: \n64: ```python\n65: from dify_plugin import ToolProvider\n66: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n67: \n68: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n69:     def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n70:         try:\n71:             \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n72:         except Exception as e:\n73:             raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n74: ```\n75: \n76: (OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n77: \n78: ## Tool implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n79: \n80: ```python\n81: from collections.abc import Generator\n82: from typing import Any\n83: from dify_plugin import Tool\n84: from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\n85: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n86: \n87: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n88:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n89:         result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n90:         yield self.create_json_message(result)\n91: \n92:     def execute(\n93:         self,\n94:         router_url=None,\n95:         workload_manager_url=None,\n96:         language=\"python\",\n97:         code_interpreter_id=None,\n98:         session_id=None,\n99:         code=None,\n100:         command=None,\n101:         session_reuse=False,\n102:         **kwargs\n103:     ): ...\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Plugin dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n107: \n108: ```\n109: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n110: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ## PCAP analyzer вҖ” application structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n114: \n115: | File | Role |\n116: |------|------|\n117: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n118: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n119: | `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n120: | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n121: | `README.md` | Documentation |\n122: \n123: ## FastAPI application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n124: \n125: ### Globals / config (selected)\n126: \n127: | Name | Source | Default / value |\n128: |------|--------|-----------------|\n129: | `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | required at startup |\n130: | `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n131: | `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n132: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n133: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n134: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n135: | `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n136: | `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n137: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n138: \n139: ### Core classes / functions\n140: \n141: ```python\n142: class SandboxRunner:\n143:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n144:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n145:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n146:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n147:     def stop(self): ...\n148: \n149: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\n150: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\n151: def build_planner_agent(llm): ...\n152: def build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n153: \n154: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\n155: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n156: def _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n157: def _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n158: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n159: \n160: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n161:     script: str\n162:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n163:     report: str\n164: \n165: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer вҖ” Env-Only Config\")\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### FastAPI endpoints\n169: \n170: | Method | Path | Signature / behavior |\n171: |--------|------|----------------------|\n172: | (event) | startup | `on_startup()` вҶ’ builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n173: | `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` вҶ’ `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n174: \n175: ### Imports of note\n176: \n177: ```python\n178: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n179: from pydantic import BaseModel\n180: import uvicorn\n181: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n182: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n183: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n184: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n185: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ## Kubernetes deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n189: \n190: - `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n191: - Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n192: - Container port `8000` TCP\n193: - Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n194: - Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n195: - Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n196: \n197: ## Dockerfile highlights\n198: \n199: - Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n200: - `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n201: - Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` вҶ’ `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` вҶ’ `./`\n202: - `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n203: - `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n204: \n205: ## PCAP example Python dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n206: \n207: Pinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n208: \n209: *(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n\n(End of file - total 209 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Integrations вҖ” Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n\n## Dify plugin вҖ” file map\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n| `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n| `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n\n## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n\nFrom source:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md","time":{"start":1775897713547,"end":1775897713568}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897713583,"sessionID":"ses_2843f9435ffeZ3zCsY9nzwDCy7","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc0984e001QxP90GyFbZyeOp","messageID":"msg_d7bc08d1e001WTiCfeDOh75HX2","sessionID":"ses_2843f9435ffeZ3zCsY9nzwDCy7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-02da7939abf34c9ab848c8e38af88936","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CLI Build Command Design\n2: \n3: **AR**: AR-021 вҖ” CLI build е‘Ҫд»Ө  \n4: **Module**: cmd/cli  \n5: **Language**: Python  \n6: **Size**: M\n7: \n8: ## Overview\n9: \n10: The `build` command is a core component of the AgentCube CLI that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces. It supports both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds, with automatic version management and comprehensive error handling.\n11: \n12: ## Architecture\n13: \n14: ### Component Diagram\n15: \n16: ```\n17: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n18: в”Ӯ   CLI (Typer)   в”Ӯ\n19: в”Ӯ  main.py     в”Ӯ\n20: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n21:        в”Ӯ build()\n22:        в–ј\n23: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n24: в”Ӯ  BuildRuntime       в”Ӯ\n25: в”Ӯ  build_runtime.py   в”Ӯ\n26: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n27:        в”Ӯ\n28:        в”ңв”Җв”Җв–ә MetadataService\n29:        в”Ӯ    в””в”Җв”Җ load_metadata()\n30:        в”Ӯ    в””в”Җв”Җ save_metadata()\n31:        в”Ӯ\n32:        в””в”Җв”Җв–ә DockerService\n33:             в””в”Җв”Җ check_docker_available()\n34:             в””в”Җв”Җ build_image()\n35:             в””в”Җв”Җ get_image_info()\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ### Key Components\n39: \n40: 1. **CLI Layer** (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n41:    - Typer command definition\n42:    - User input validation\n43:    - Error handling and user feedback\n44: \n45: 2. **Runtime Layer** (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n46:    - Build orchestration\n47:    - Version management\n48:    - Build mode selection\n49: \n50: 3. **Service Layer**\n51:    - `MetadataService`: Metadata persistence and loading\n52:    - `DockerService`: Docker operations (build, push, etc.)\n53: \n54: ## Data Structures\n55: \n56: ### BuildOptions\n57: \n58: Dictionary containing build command options:\n59: \n60: ```python\n61: {\n62:     \"proxy\": Optional[str],          # Proxy URL for dependency resolution\n63:     \"cloud_provider\": Optional[str], # Cloud provider name (e.g., \"huawei\")\n64:     \"output\": Optional[str],         # Output path for build artifacts\n65: }\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### BuildResult\n69: \n70: Dictionary containing build output information:\n71: \n72: ```python\n73: {\n74:     \"image_name\": str,       # Full image name with tag (e.g., \"agent:1.0.0\")\n75:     \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (short form, 12 chars)\n76:     \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"512.34 MB\")\n77:     \"size_bytes\": int,       # Size in bytes\n78:     \"build_time\": float,     # Unix timestamp of build completion\n79: }\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### AgentMetadata Fields (Build-related)\n83: \n84: Relevant fields from `AgentMetadata` for build operations:\n85: \n86: ```python\n87: agent_name: str              # Used as image name\n88: version: Optional[str]       # Semantic version (auto-incremented)\n89: build_mode: str              # \"local\" or \"cloud\"\n90: image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]  # Build result storage\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ## API Contracts\n94: \n95: ### BuildRuntime.build()\n96: \n97: ```python\n98: def build(\n99:     self,\n100:     workspace_path: Path,\n101:     **options: Any\n102: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n103: ```\n104: \n105: **Purpose**: Build a container image from a packaged agent workspace.\n106: \n107: **Parameters**:\n108: - `workspace_path` (Path): Path to the agent workspace directory\n109: - `options` (Dict[str, Any]): Build options including proxy, cloud_provider, output\n110: \n111: **Returns**: `BuildResult` dictionary\n112: \n113: **Behavior**:\n114: 1. Loads metadata from workspace\n115: 2. Validates build prerequisites (Dockerfile exists, Docker available)\n116: 3. Increments version (with rollback on failure)\n117: 4. Executes build based on `build_mode` in metadata\n118: 5. Updates metadata with build results\n119: 6. Returns build result\n120: \n121: **Raises**:\n122: - `ValueError`: If Dockerfile not found or prerequisites not met\n123: - `RuntimeError`: If Docker is not available or build fails\n124: - `FileNotFoundError`: If metadata file not found\n125: \n126: ### BuildRuntime._build_local()\n127: \n128: ```python\n129: def _build_local(\n130:     self,\n131:     workspace_path: Path,\n132:     metadata: AgentMetadata,\n133:     options: Dict[str, Any]\n134: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n135: ```\n136: \n137: **Purpose**: Build image using local Docker daemon.\n138: \n139: **Parameters**:\n140: - `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace (used as build context)\n141: - `metadata` (AgentMetadata): Agent metadata containing name and version\n142: - `options` (Dict[str, Any]): Build options (proxy support)\n143: \n144: **Behavior**:\n145: - Constructs image name from `agent_name` and `version`\n146: - Optionally adds proxy build arguments if proxy provided\n147: - Delegates to `DockerService.build_image()`\n148: - Adds image name to result\n149: \n150: ### BuildRuntime._build_cloud()\n151: \n152: ```python\n153: def _build_cloud(\n154:     self,\n155:     workspace_path: Path,\n156:     metadata: AgentMetadata,\n157:     options: Dict[str, Any]\n158: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Purpose**: Build image in cloud provider (placeholder implementation).\n162: \n163: **Parameters**:\n164: - `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace\n165: - `metadata` (AgentMetadata): Agent metadata\n166: - `options` (Dict[str, Any]): Build options including cloud_provider\n167: \n168: **Behavior**:\n169: - Returns placeholder build result with cloud provider prefix\n170: - Logs cloud provider name\n171: \n172: ### BuildRuntime._increment_version()\n173: \n174: ```python\n175: def _increment_version(\n176:     self,\n177:     workspace_path: Path,\n178:     metadata: AgentMetadata\n179: ) -> str\n180: ```\n181: \n182: **Purpose**: Increment agent version before build.\n183: \n184: **Parameters**:\n185: - `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace (for saving metadata)\n186: - `metadata` (AgentMetadata): Agent metadata to modify\n187: \n188: **Returns**: New version string\n189: \n190: **Version Rules**:\n191: 1. **Semantic version** (X.Y.Z): Increment patch (Z)\n192: 2. **Semantic version with prerelease** (X.Y.Z-N.suffix): Increment prerelease number (N)\n193: 3. **Non-semantic version**: Append \".1\"\n194: 4. **No version**: Set to \"0.1.0\"\n195: \n196: **Examples**:\n197: - `\"1.0.0\"` вҶ’ `\"1.0.1\"`\n198: - `\"1.0.0-alpha.1\"` вҶ’ `\"1.0.0-alpha.2\"`\n199: - `\"custom-version\"` вҶ’ `\"custom-version-1\"`\n200: - `None` вҶ’ `\"0.1.0\"`\n201: \n202: ### BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()\n203: \n204: ```python\n205: def _validate_build_prerequisites(\n206:     self,\n207:     workspace_path: Path\n208: ) -> None\n209: ```\n210: \n211: **Purpose**: Ensure workspace is ready for build.\n212: \n213: **Parameters**:\n214: - `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace\n215: \n216: **Checks**:\n217: 1. Dockerfile exists at `{workspace_path}/Dockerfile`\n218: 2. Docker daemon is available and running\n219: \n220: **Raises**:\n221: - `ValueError`: If Dockerfile not found\n222: - `RuntimeError`: If Docker not available\n223: \n224: ### BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata()\n225: \n226: ```python\n227: def _update_build_metadata(\n228:     self,\n229:     workspace_path: Path,\n230:     metadata: AgentMetadata,\n231:     build_result: Dict[str, str],\n232:     tag: str = \"latest\"\n233: ) -> None\n234: ```\n235: \n236: **Purpose**: Store build results in metadata.\n237: \n238: **Parameters**:\n239: - `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace\n240: - `metadata` (AgentMetadata): Agent metadata to update\n241: - `build_result` (Dict[str, str]): Build result from DockerService\n242: - `tag` (str): Image tag (default \"latest\")\n243: \n244: **Behavior**:\n245: - Merges build result into `metadata.image` dictionary\n246: - Saves updated metadata to workspace\n247: \n248: ### DockerService.build_image()\n249: \n250: ```python\n251: def build_image(\n252:     self,\n253:     dockerfile_path: Path,\n254:     context_path: Path,\n255:     image_name: str,\n256:     tag: str = \"latest\",\n257:     build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n258: ) -> Dict[str, str]\n259: ```\n260: \n261: **Purpose**: Build Docker image using Docker SDK.\n262: \n263: **Parameters**:\n264: - `dockerfile_path` (Path): Path to Dockerfile\n265: - `context_path` (Path): Build context directory\n266: - `image_name` (str): Base image name\n267: - `tag` (str): Image tag\n268: - `build_args` (Optional[Dict[str, str]]): Docker build arguments\n269: \n270: **Returns**: Dictionary with image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time\n271: \n272: **Behavior**:\n273: - Constructs full image name: `{image_name}:{tag}`\n274: - Calls `docker.from_env().images.build()`\n275: - Retrieves image information using `get_image_info()`\n276: - Adds build timestamp\n277: \n278: ## Error Handling\n279: \n280: ### Error Hierarchy\n281: \n282: ```\n283: Exception\n284: в”ңв”Җв”Җ ValueError (User input errors)\n285: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ \"Dockerfile not found in workspace\"\n286: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ \"No metadata file found in workspace\"\n287: в”ңв”Җв”Җ RuntimeError (System errors)\n288: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ \"Docker is not available or not running\"\n289: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ \"Failed to build Docker image\"\n290: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ \"Failed to log in to Docker registry\"\n291: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ \"Failed to tag Docker image\"\n292: в””в”Җв”Җ FileNotFoundError\n293:     в””в”Җв”Җ Metadata file not found\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ### Error Handling Strategy\n297: \n298: #### CLI Layer (main.py)\n299: \n300: ```python\n301: def build(...):\n302:     try:\n303:         runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n304:         result = runtime.build(workspace_path, **options)\n305:         console.print_success(result)\n306:     except Exception as e:\n307:         _handle_error(e, \"building image\", verbose)\n308: ```\n309: \n310: #### Runtime Layer (build_runtime.py)\n311: \n312: ```python\n313: def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n314:     original_version = metadata.version\n315:     self._increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)\n316:     \n317:     try:\n318:         result = self._execute_build(...)\n319:         self._update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, result)\n320:         return result\n321:     except Exception as e:\n322:         if original_version != metadata.version:\n323:             self._revert_version(workspace_path, original_version)\n324:         raise\n325: ```\n326: \n327: #### Version Reversion on Failure\n328: \n329: - Store original version before increment\n330: - On build failure, restore original version\n331: - Log warning: \"Build failed, reverting version from X to Y\"\n332: - Save reverted metadata\n333: \n334: #### DockerService Error Handling\n335: \n336: ```python\n337: def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n338:     try:\n339:         self.client.ping()\n340:         return True\n341:     except DockerException as e:\n342:         logger.warning(f\"Docker not available: {e}\")\n343:         return False\n344: \n345: def build_image(self, ...):\n346:     if not self.check_docker_available():\n347:         raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n348:     \n349:     try:\n350:         image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(...)\n351:         return self.get_image_info(full_image_name)\n352:     except DockerException as e:\n353:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to build Docker image: {e}\") from e\n354: ```\n355: \n356: ### User-Facing Error Messages\n357: \n358: | Error | Message | Exit Code |\n359: |-------|---------|-----------|\n360: | Dockerfile not found | \"Dockerfile not found in workspace. Run 'pack' first.\" | 1 |\n361: | Docker unavailable | \"Error building image: Docker is not available or not running\" | 1 |\n362: | Build failure | \"Error building image: Failed to build Docker image: {error}\" | 1 |\n363: | Metadata not found | \"Error building image: No metadata file found in {workspace}\" | 1 |\n364: \n365: ## Testing Strategy\n366: \n367: ### Unit Tests\n368: \n369: #### Test: BuildRuntime._increment_version()\n370: \n371: ```python\n372: def test_increment_semantic_version():\n373:     metadata = AgentMetadata(\n374:         agent_name=\"test\",\n375:         entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n376:         version=\"1.0.0\"\n377:     )\n378:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n379:     new_version = runtime._increment_version(Path(\"/tmp\"), metadata)\n380:     assert new_version == \"1.0.1\"\n381:     assert metadata.version == \"1.0.1\"\n382: \n383: def test_increment_prerelease_version():\n384:     metadata = AgentMetadata(\n385:         agent_name=\"test\",\n386:         entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n387:         version=\"1.0.0-alpha.1\"\n388:     )\n389:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n390:     new_version = runtime._increment_version(Path(\"/tmp\"), metadata)\n391:     assert new_version == \"1.0.0-alpha.2\"\n392: \n393: def test_increment_custom_version():\n394:     metadata = AgentMetadata(\n395:         agent_name=\"test\",\n396:         entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n397:         version=\"custom-version\"\n398:     )\n399:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n400:     new_version = runtime._increment_version(Path(\"/tmp\"), metadata)\n401:     assert new_version == \"custom-version-1\"\n402: \n403: def test_increment_no_version():\n404:     metadata = AgentMetadata(\n405:         agent_name=\"test\",\n406:         entrypoint=\"python main.py\"\n407:     )\n408:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n409:     new_version = runtime._increment_version(Path(\"/tmp\"), metadata)\n410:     assert new_version == \"0.1.0\"\n411: ```\n412: \n413: #### Test: BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()\n414: \n415: ```python\n416: def test_validate_missing_dockerfile(tmp_path):\n417:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n418:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Dockerfile not found\"):\n419:         runtime._validate_build_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n420: \n421: def test_validate_docker_unavailable(tmp_path, mocker):\n422:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n423:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"FROM python:3.10\")\n424:     mocker.patch.object(runtime.docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=False)\n425:     with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"Docker is not available\"):\n426:         runtime._validate_build_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n427: ```\n428: \n429: #### Test: BuildRuntime.build() - Version Reversion\n430: \n431: ```python\n432: def test_build_reverts_version_on_failure(tmp_path, mocker):\n433:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n434:         \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nversion: 1.0.0\"\n435:     )\n436:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"FROM python:3.10\")\n437:     \n438:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n439:     mocker.patch.object(runtime, \"_build_local\", side_effect=RuntimeError(\"Build failed\"))\n440:     mocker.patch.object(runtime.docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=True)\n441:     \n442:     with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n443:         runtime.build(tmp_path)\n444:     \n445:     metadata = runtime.metadata_service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n446:     assert metadata.version == \"1.0.0\"  # Reverted\n447: ```\n448: \n449: ### Integration Tests\n450: \n451: #### Test: End-to-End Local Build\n452: \n453: ```python\n454: @pytest.mark.integration\n455: def test_e2e_build_local(tmp_path):\n456:     # Create valid workspace\n457:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n458:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"FROM python:3.10\\nCOPY main.py .\\nCMD python main.py\")\n459:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n460:         \"agent_name: test-agent\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nversion: 1.0.0\"\n461:     )\n462:     \n463:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n464:     result = runtime.build(tmp_path)\n465:     \n466:     assert result[\"image_name\"] == \"test-agent:1.0.1\"\n467:     assert \"image_id\" in result\n468:     assert result[\"image_size\"] != \"0.00 B\"\n469:     \n470:     metadata = runtime.metadata_service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n471:     assert metadata.version == \"1.0.1\"\n472:     assert metadata.image is not None\n473: ```\n474: \n475: #### Test: Build with Proxy\n476: \n477: ```python\n478: def test_build_with_proxy(tmp_path, mocker):\n479:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"FROM python:3.10\")\n480:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n481:         \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\"\n482:     )\n483:     \n484:     runtime = BuildRuntime()\n485:     build_mock = mocker.patch.object(runtime.docker_service, \"build_image\", return_value={\n486:         \"image_name\": \"test:latest\",\n487:         \"image_id\": \"abc123\",\n488:         \"image_size\": \"100 MB\",\n489:     })\n490:     \n491:     runtime.build(tmp_path, proxy=\"http://proxy.example.com:8080\")\n492:     \n493:     build_mock.assert_called_once()\n494:     call_args = build_mock.call_args\n495:     assert call_args.kwargs[\"build_args\"][\"HTTP_PROXY\"] == \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"\n496:     assert call_args.kwargs[\"build_args\"][\"HTTPS_PROXY\"] == \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"\n497: ```\n498: \n499: ### Mocking Strategy\n500: \n501: #### DockerService Mock\n502: \n503: ```python\n504: @pytest.fixture\n505: def mock_docker_service(mocker):\n506:     service = mocker.MagicMock(spec=DockerService)\n507:     service.check_docker_available.return_value = True\n508:     service.build_image.return_value = {\n509:         \"image_name\": \"test:1.0.0\",\n510:         \"image_id\": \"abc123def456\",\n511:         \"image_size\": \"512.34 MB\",\n512:         \"build_time\": 1234567890.0,\n513:     }\n514:     service.get_image_info.return_value = {\n515:         \"image_name\": \"test:1.0.0\",\n516:         \"image_id\": \"abc123def456\",\n517:         \"image_size\": \"512.34 MB\",\n518:         \"size_bytes\": 536870912,\n519:     }\n520:     return service\n521: ```\n522: \n523: #### MetadataService Mock\n524: \n525: ```python\n526: @pytest.fixture\n527: def mock_metadata_service(tmp_path, mocker):\n528:     service = mocker.MagicMock(spec=MetadataService)\n529:     \n530:     def load_side_effect(path):\n531:         return AgentMetadata(\n532:             agent_name=\"test\",\n533:             entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n534:             version=\"1.0.0\",\n535:             build_mode=\"local\"\n536:         )\n537:     \n538:     service.load_metadata.side_effect = load_side_effect\n539:     service.save_metadata = mocker.MagicMock()\n540:     return service\n541: ```\n542: \n543: ### Test Coverage Goals\n544: \n545: | Component | Target Coverage |\n546: |-----------|-----------------|\n547: | build_runtime.py | 90%+ |\n548: | docker_service.py | 85%+ |\n549: | main.py (build command) | 80%+ |\n550: \n551: ### Test Execution\n552: \n553: ```bash\n554: # Run all tests\n555: pytest tests/\n556: \n557: # Run with coverage\n558: pytest --cov=agentcube.runtime.build_runtime --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service\n559: \n560: # Run integration tests only\n561: pytest -m integration\n562: \n563: # Run unit tests only\n564: pytest -m \"not integration\"\n565: ```\n566: \n567: ## CLI Usage\n568: \n569: ### Basic Usage\n570: \n571: ```bash\n572: # Build from current directory\n573: kubectl-agentcube build\n574: \n575: # Build from specific workspace\n576: kubectl-agentcube build -f /path/to/workspace\n577: \n578: # Build with verbose output\n579: kubectl-agentcube build --verbose\n580: \n581: # Build with proxy\n582: kubectl-agentcube build --proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080\n583: \n584: # Build with cloud provider\n585: kubectl-agentcube build --cloud-provider huawei\n586: ```\n587: \n588: ### Prerequisites\n589: \n590: 1. Workspace must be packed (contains `Dockerfile` and `agent_metadata.yaml`)\n591: 2. Docker daemon must be running (for local builds)\n592: 3. Sufficient disk space for image storage\n593: \n594: ### Output\n595: \n596: ```\n597: в Ӣ Building image...\n598: вң“ Successfully built image\n599:   Image name: test-agent:1.0.1\n600:   Image ID: abc123def456\n601:   Image size: 512.34 MB\n602: ```\n603: \n604: ## Dependencies\n605: \n606: ### Required\n607: \n608: - `docker>=6.0.0`: Docker SDK for Python\n609: - `pydantic>=2.0.0`: Data validation (via AgentMetadata)\n610: - `pyyaml>=6.0.0`: YAML parsing (via MetadataService)\n611: \n612: ### Optional\n613: \n614: - `kubernetes>=28.0.0`: Kubernetes support (for cloud builds)\n615: \n616: ## Future Enhancements\n617: \n618: 1. **Multi-platform builds**: Support for `--platform` flag (linux/amd64, linux/arm64)\n619: 2. **Build caching**: Layer caching optimization for faster builds\n620: 3. **Parallel builds**: Support for building multiple workspaces concurrently\n621: 4. **Build hooks**: Pre-build and post-build script execution\n622: 5. **Cloud provider integrations**: Full implementations for AWS, GCP, Azure\n623: 6. **Build metrics**: Detailed build time and size analytics\n624: 7. **Build optimization**: Automatic dependency analysis and layer optimization\n\n(End of file - total 624 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CLI Build Command Design\n\n**AR**: AR-021 вҖ” CLI build е‘Ҫд»Ө  \n**Module**: cmd/cli  \n**Language**: Python  \n**Size**: M\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `build` command is a core component of the AgentCube CLI that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces. It supports both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds, with automatic version management and comprehensive error handling.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ   CLI (Typer)   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  main.py     в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/design.md","time":{"start":1775897713545,"end":1775897713580}}}}
